Description: Wall sherd with handle root of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery cup; pale brown clay with some silver mica; interior streaky reddish-black; exterior: handle zone reserved; glazed below and around handle; inscription on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Aphrodite (Naukratis), Context Φ3(?) (?)
Curator's comments: Worn pencil mark on front, perhaps 33.; most probably 339.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.348)
